==English==
===Etymology===
From Arabic {{ARchar|[[حديث]]}} (''ħadí:θ'', 'Prophetic tradition') < {{ARchar|[[حدث]]}} (''ħáddaθa'', 'to tell,' 'to relate,' 'to report').

===Noun===
'''hadith'''  (''plural:'' ''hadith'' or ''hadiths'')

#(''Islam'') the [[collected]] [[saying]]s and [[action]]s of [[Muhammad]] and his companions; used to [[determine]] the [[Sunna]] ([[Muslim]] way of life).

